{"ts":"2026-07-19T15:37:46.603Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T15:37:46.603Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-19T15:37:46.603Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Evidence: PmClient.create/update/close now take contract-derived typed option bags (PmCreateActionOptions/PmUpdateActionOptions/PmClientCloseActionOptions) built by OptionsFromContracts over const-asserted *_SOURCE tuples in tool-option-contracts.ts — same objects that build the runtime tables, pinned by a parity spec; CLOSE_ACTION_OPTION_KEYS single-sources the close schema + close type. Typo/wrong-shape rejection enforced by tests/types/typed-action-inputs.test-d.ts via tsconfig.typetests.json wired into pnpm typecheck (CI gate). ListProjectedItem gains typed ListProjectedItemCore (row.id string|undefined, never unknown). No runtime behavior change; PmClient.run stays the wide escape hatch; custom schema fields keep the repeatable field option. Remainder honestly out of scope here: claim/release/copy/delete/restore convenience bags are still Record-based."}]}],"before_hash":"53c114be9d19b3a749a213c911ad15437b9a70e0dcab272c3a87bc57713127ff","after_hash":"04144155978f27a4e6a70c3edd9307e5cd01525a1afdb87b09bf2111c407d2aa"}
