{"ts":"2026-07-19T15:38:36.275Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T15:38:36.275Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-19T15:38:36.272Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Deriving compile-time types from runtime contract tables requires const-asserted sources; widened annotations (X[] = [...]) erase literals permanently. Pattern: const SOURCE = [...] as const satisfies readonly T[]; export runtime clones + typeof SOURCE types, and pin them together with a runtime parity spec. Interfaces in composed option bags break implicit index-signature assignability to Record-based dispatch layers — use object type literals."}]}],"before_hash":"a5f2aea26018428f50856b71af8a014fe20ed2748826fc7b9e2aacdc3ae4ed42","after_hash":"aa1b5b78570826e8676bb7e4469fbab75130757ec2e7acb857c35ab552bed3c3"}
